description.narrative: In 2021, thanks to UNICEF support, the Ministry of Health adopted and launched national guidance for health workers to better detect and respond to child victims of violence and abuse, and 100% of the 840 social workers in country are now specifically skilled for CP related social work. In total,1,615 professionals from the social welfare, education, health, justice and security sector strengthened their capacities on Child protection, with sector specific and coordination tools. Child protection Platforms for Prevention have been set up in Child Protection Department Committees (CDPE) in 5 regions. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:02/02/2022
